title: Santa Ana River Wash Plan Land Exchange Act
content: Santa Ana River Wash Plan Land Exchange Act This bill directs the Department of the Interior: (1) to quitclaim to the San Bernardino Valley Water Conservation District in California approximately 327 acres of identified federal land administered by the Bureau of Land Management. And (2) in exchange for such land, to accept from the Conservation District a conveyance of approximately 310 acres of its land.
